article_text:
"A deeply unpopular Republican Party is nonetheless gaining strength heading into the midterms, as the American public's frustration with Mr. Obama has manifested itself in low ratings for his handling of foreign policy and terrorism," the New York Times reported the other day, in a feature on its website about the results of the latest Times/CBS News poll.

The poll found "President Obama's approval ratings are very similar to those of George W. Bush in September 2006." Actually, on the whole they're...
